8.3.22  9:42 pm   A couple weeks or months ago i asked a question because i found that every cool melodic idea i had seemed to go with a chord sequence that starts on the 4 chord. And i asked for advice on replicating the tension that starting on the 4 brings, without starting the chorus in all of my songs on the 4 chord. You suggested i transcribe a bunch of songs that i like to figure out what they're doing. I went through a big playlist i had of my favorite songs, and what i learned is, maybe i just really like songs with choruses that start on the 4?

      I went through 65 of them and 21 unambiguously had a chorus starting on the 4. Which seems like a lot. Another 15 of them started with a 6m into a 4, mostly going 6m 4 1 5.

      I don't tend to write a lot of songs with that progression because i wrote about a billion that way when i was younger. So that's over half of the songs (36/65) covered by the two harmonic ideas i am already doing way too much. Of the rest of the songs, wh ile they're good, they generally don't have the immediate tension that songs starting on the 4 do. Maybe it shouldn't be surprising that different chords sound different. But it seems like the best approach is either to deal with all my songs being a bit similar, or to accept that they won't be exciting in the same manner as (for example) Everytime We Touch. Does that seem like a fair assessment

8.3.22  7:52 pm   If there are infinite universes that split apart and branch out whenever each of us make a choice, then innumerable universes must exist where I am dead, by having given in to my inexplicable slight urge, when walking on the sidewalk, to jump in front of a car; when by a lighted kitchen stove, to mash my face into the fire; when on a bridge high up between two ledges, to help myself over to the opposite side of the railing and let go; when by a spinning blade, to insert a part of my body or one of my articles of clothing into the thing; or any of a number of other possible outcomes reaching insane proportions. Of course, since I have mentally developed in such a way that I can and choose to overpower these urges, none of these gruesome scenarios occur. This raises the question: Do these alternate universes even exist?
